    ADOBECODEBANC
     ^        ^
    begin    end

&gt; When you are doing that, unknowingly your code did not take B (at index 9) into account and end pointer reached A (at index 10).

Afterward when begin pointer reached B (at index 4) and you incremented counter, your end pointer was not able to find any other B.

    ADOBECODEBANC
        ^     ^
      begin  end

Hence you got the answer as **ADOBEC**

